            "detailed_description": "<img src=\"https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steam/apps/1032280/extras/Voice-controlled_New_small2.png?t=1599686794\" /><br><br><strong><i>Developed by 2 Students</i></strong><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">The Game</h2><br><strong><i>The Voice Inside</i></strong> is a <strong>completely voice-controlled, psychological horror adventure game</strong>, developed for a whole new voice-driven game experience. You can choose between <strong>more than 30 voice commands</strong> to navigate a nearly blind character, solve puzzles and perform actions to recover the light in a dark, infected and abstract world. The character reacts to simple commands, such as 'move', 'run','45 left/right', 'show commands' and many more. A <i>voice inside</i> the game will guide and help you to find a way out.<br>Just listen, follow your intuition and give the right commands to reach your goal!<h2 class=\"bb_tag\"> Voice Commands</h2><strong>Over 30 voice commands can be used to navigate your character</strong><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\">Examples:<li><strong>Move (go/walk)</strong> – normal speed<br></li><li><strong>Run (hurry)</strong>– let your character run <br></li><li><strong>Stop (wait/hold on)</strong> - stop the character immediately <br></li><li><strong>Sneak </strong> - slow movement to avoid the enemy’s attention <br></li><li><strong>Speed Up</strong> – increase your current speed<br></li><li><strong>Turn Right</strong> (right) – turns 90° right</li></ul>and many more...<br>Just listen to 'the voice inside', it tells you what to do.<br><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Supports</strong>: Voice-only, Controller, Voice-Controller mixed</li></ul><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Requirements</h2><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><strong>Headset/Microphone</strong> (no keyboard/controller needed, voice-activated!)<br></li><li><strong> Windows 10!</strong> <strong>or</strong> use a controlller for all Windows OS<br><br><img src=\"https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/steam/apps/1032280/extras/Header_ADK_TVI2_banner_tiny_roundCorners.png?t=1599686794\" /></li></ul>",
